            [
                'id'           => 1,
                'title'        => 'Welcome to My Corner of the Internet',
                'slug'         => 'welcome-to-my-corner-of-the-internet',
                'excerpt'      => 'A personal note from Ruth on why she started this blog, what you can expect, and what My Perfect Stitch really stands for.',
                'body'         => '<p>I have been meaning to write this post for a long time. Not because I did not know what to say — but because I wanted to say it properly.</p><p>This blog is my space. A place where I talk about the things that matter to me: building a business from the ground up, the craft of making things with your hands, what it means to be a Zambian woman carving out space in the design and manufacturing world, and the honest, sometimes uncomfortable lessons that come with entrepreneurship.</p><h2>What You Will Find Here</h2><p>I am not interested in writing a blog that is just marketing. You can find that everywhere. What I want to write — and what I hope you want to read — is something more real.</p><p>I will write about the behind-the-scenes of My Perfect Stitch: the ideas that worked, the ones that did not, the pieces I am most proud of, and the process that goes into every commission. I will write about what it feels like to run a growing enterprise in Zambia — the challenges, the small victories, and the community that makes it all possible.</p><h2>Who This Is For</h2><p>If you are a customer of My Perfect Stitch — welcome. I hope this gives you a deeper sense of the people and ideas behind the things you have bought or are thinking of buying.</p><p>If you are an entrepreneur, especially a young African woman thinking about making the leap — this is very much for you. I was you not long ago. I still remember what it felt like to want something this much and not yet know how to reach it.</p><p>If you are simply curious about African design, craftsmanship, and what a purpose-driven business actually looks like from the inside — pull up a chair. I think you will find something worth staying for.</p><p>Thank you for being here.</p><p><em>— Ruth</em></p>',
                'cover_image'  => $u.'1590650153855-d9e808231d41'.$q,
                'published'    => 1,
                'published_at' => '2026-05-26 16:49:02',
