                'exec_image'  => $u.'1578509566163-068acd11b8e7'.$q,
                'about_col1'  => 'The brief was to create a co-working lounge that felt unmistakably Zambian without relying on cliché. The client — a creative and technology hub in the heart of Lusaka — wanted a space that young African professionals would be proud to work from, photograph, and share. What we built was an interior that draws its language from the land: ochre walls, woven textiles, dark timber, and light that moves.',
                'about_col2'  => 'Every piece of furniture was designed and made by My Perfect Stitch in the studio. The upholstery combines locally woven chitengi fabric with full-grain leather in a palette drawn from the Zambian savanna. The result is a space that is immediately recognisable as African — not because of what is displayed, but because of what it is made from.',
                'exec_col1'   => 'The project was completed in eleven weeks from brief to handover, working around the hub\'s live operations. We built in modular sections — each zone of the lounge was delivered and installed as a complete unit — so the space was never entirely out of service during the fit-out.',
                'exec_col2'   => 'Workstations were designed to convert between individual focus work and collaborative table arrangements. The reception desk is a single piece of solid Mahogany, twelve feet wide, with a hand-stitched leather top surface. Since opening, the lounge has been featured in two regional design publications and has become one of the most photographed interiors in Lusaka.',
                'category'    => 'Interiors',
                'sort_order'  => 5,
                'published'   => 1,
                'created_at'  => '2026-05-28 13:17:34',
